    <h2>Customise the Customer’s Journey</h2>
    <p>Between retargeting and a daily-impression cap, there is no solution that allows you to target an <i>individual</i>. There is no drag-and-drop solution that lets you show a sequence of creatives to individual users (
    <span class="tooltip tooltip-effect-5">
        <span class="tooltip-item">cookies</span>
        <span class="tooltip-content clearfix">
            <span class="tooltip-text">Desktop users.</span>
        </span>
    </span>,
    <span class="tooltip tooltip-effect-5">
        <span class="tooltip-item">IDFA</span>
        <span class="tooltip-content clearfix">
            <span class="tooltip-text">Android users.</span>
        </span>
    </span>,
    <span class="tooltip tooltip-effect-5">
        <span class="tooltip-item">AAID</span>
        <span class="tooltip-content clearfix">
            <span class="tooltip-text">Apple's version of cookies for mobile, i.e. <i>iPhone and iPad</i>.</span>
        </span>
    </span>).</p>
    <p>Using our “Story Board” UI, you can easily generate:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Day 1: show “get 5% on these red shoes...”</li>
        <li>Day 2: show “get 10% on the red shoes...”</li>
        <li>Day 3: show “Holiday special 15% off on these red shoes”</li>
    </ul>
    <p>etc. CRM or ERP data can easily be integrated to synchronise with your shopping cart.</p>
    <p>Limitation:<br> Google’s AdX will not allow 
    <span class="tooltip tooltip-effect-5">
        <span class="tooltip-item">Pii</span>
        <span class="tooltip-content clearfix">
            <span class="tooltip-text">Personally identifiable information.</span>
        </span>
    </span>
, so &lt;First Name&gt; &lt;Last Name&gt; is not allowed. But &lt;City&gt; can be used.</p>
